li><a href="http://www.entry.com/entry-services.html">Services</a></li></ul> <a href="http://www.entry.com/quotes-case-studies.html" class="btn btn-lg btn-primary btn-block">CASE STUDIES</a> <a href="http://entry-software.helpdocsonline.com/#teamheadquarters-video-training-library" target="_blank" class="btn btn-lg btn-primary btn-block">VIDEO LIBRARY</a> <a href="http://signup.entry.com/trial-demo-both-teamheadquarters" class="btn btn-lg btn-block btn-success">TRIAL OR DEMO</a> </div><div class="col-md-9"> <div class="jumbotron"> <img class="pull-right" src="http://www.entry.com/img/thq-apple-114x114.png" alt="teamheadquarters gizmo" width="114" height="114"> <h1>TeamHeadquarters Videos</h1> </div></div><div class="container media-grouping media-area"> <div class="row"> <div class="col-md-8"> <div class="media panel"> <video class="pull-right" width="320" height="240" poster="movies/my-work-dashboard.jpg" controls="controls" preload="none"> <source src="movies/my-work-dashboard.mp4" type="video/mp4"> Your browser does not support the HTML5 video tag </video> <h3>My Work Dashboard</h3> <p>Instructional video on the My Work Dashboard. The TeamHeadquarters my work dashboard presents five channels to the end-user. These channels are: tasks due, tickets due, work scheduled, this week, and recent activity.</p></div><div class="media panel"> <video class="pull-right" width="320" height="240" poster="movies/my-calendar.jpg" controls="controls" preload="none"> <source src="movies/my-calendar.mp4"> Your browser does not support the HTML5 video tag </video> <h3>My Calendar</h3> <p>This video training session is on the TeamHeadquarters calendar.The TeamHeadquarters calendar has been designed so that you can do all of your work in one location regardless of whether it is support, operations, or planned project work.</p></div><div class="media panel"> <video class="pull-right" width="320" height="240" poster="movies/my-tickets-intro.jpg" controls="controls" preload="none"> <source src="movies/my-tickets-intro.mp4"> Your browser does not support the HTML5 video tag </video> <h3>My Tickets - Introduction</h3> <p>This video training session is an introduction to TeamHeadquarters tickets. Tickets in TeamHeadquarters are used to capture service requests, service incidents, project issues, and change requests and any variety of interactions between customers service and project teams.</p></div><div class="media panel"> <video class="pull-right" width="320" height="240" poster="movies/creating-tickets.jpg" controls="controls" preload="none"> <source src="movies/creating-tickets.mp4"> Your browser does not support the HTML5 video tag </video> <h3>Creating Tickets</h3> <p>Instructional video on Creating Tickets. Inbound tickets can be manually created by a service agent, input by the customer via our self service portal, or received via email sent to the email ticket agent.</p></div><div class="media panel"> <video class="pull-right" width="320" height="240" poster="movies/updating-tickets.jpg" controls="controls" preload="none"> <source src="movies/updating-tickets.mp4"> Your browser does not support the HTML5 video tag </video> <h3>Updating Tickets</h3> <p>Instructional video on the Ticket Updates. The TeamHeadquarters My Tickets, Ticket Update function is used to capture time, upload files, notify rosters, customers and the "notify list" of the update.</p></div><div class="media panel"> <video class="pull-right" width="320" height="240" poster="movies/moving-tickets.jpg" controls="controls" preload="none"> <source src="movies/moving-tickets.mp4"> Your browser does not support the HTML5 video tag </video> <h3>Moving Tickets</h3> <p>Instructional video on moving TeamHeadquarters tickets from one queue to another queue using either a manual approach or an automated approach.</p></div><div class="media panel"> <video class="pull-right" width="320" height="240" poster="movies/my-tasks.jpg" controls="controls" preload="none"> <source src="movies/my-tasks.mp4"> Your browser does not support the HTML5 video tag </video> <h3>My Tasks</h3> <p>Instructional video on My Tasks. TeamHeadquarters My Tasks my tasks helps the service agent manage project tasks that are assigned to them, communicate with customers, team members and the project manager and capture time against tasks.</p></div><div class="media panel"> <video class="pull-right" width="320" height="240" poster="movies/my-documents.jpg" controls="controls" preload="none"> <source src="movies/my-documents.mp4"> Your browser does not support the HTML5 video tag </video> <h3>My Documents</h3> <p>Instructional video on My Documents. TeamHeadquarters My Documents area supports the user with document storage, and a quick and easy way to find documents associated with tickets, tasks, projects, and queues.</p></div><div class="media panel"> <video class="pull-right" width="320" height="240" poster="movies/my-timesheets.jpg" controls="controls" preload="none"> <source src="movies/my-timesheets.mp4"> Your browser does not support the HTML5 video tag </video> <h3>My Timesheets</h3> <p>Instructional video on My Timesheets. The TeamHeadquarters My Timesheet function in TeamHeadquarters is a central repository of all time entries for tickets, tasks, projects and queues.</p></div><div class="media panel"> <video class="pull-right" width="320" height="240" poster="movies/my-projects-intro.jpg" controls="controls" preload="none"> <source src="movies/my-projects-intro.mp4"> Your browser does not support the HTML5 video tag </video> <h3>My Projects - Introduction</h3> <p>Instructional video on My Projects. In this video we will be introducing to headquarters project management to you. The project management portion of these training films will be broken down into a number of components.</p></div><div class="media panel"> <video class="pull-right" width="320" height="240" poster="movies/project-grid.jpg" controls="controls" preload="none"> <source src="movies/project-grid.mp4"> Your browser does not support the HTML5 video tag </video> <h3>The TeamHeadquarters Project Grid</h3> <p>Instructional video on the TeamHeadquarters Project Grid. The Grid is the launching point for all projects you are either managing or assigned to.</p></div><div class="media panel"> <video class="pull-right" width="320" height="240" poster="movies/project-dashboard.jpg" controls="controls" preload="none"> <source src="movies/project-dashboard.mp4"> Your browser does not support the HTML5 video tag </video> <h3>My Projects - Dashboard</h3> <p>Instructional video on the My Projects Dashboard. The team headquarters my projects dashboard provides the project manager and members of the project team a quick snapshot of many aspects of their projects. From the dashboard you can quickly grasp task issues, ticket issues, and see recent activity.</p></div><div class="media panel"> <video class="pull-right" width="320" height="240" poster="movies/creating-projects.jpg" controls="controls" preload="none"> <source src="movies/creating-projects.mp4"> Your browser does not support the HTML5 video tag </video> <h3>Creating a TeamHeadquarters Project</h3> <p>This video is about Creating a TeamHeadquarters Project. The purpose of the TeamHeadquarters project management system is to:</p><ol> <li>Consolidate all project and non-project work in one application;</li><li>Provide end users all project task and support requests in a single system which allows them to prioritize action;</li><li>Report on resources across both service desk and project management;</li><li>To provide the project manager with accurate resource allocation information at the time of task assignment</li></ol> </div><div class="media panel"> <video class="pull-right" width="320" height="240" poster="movies/gantt-1.jpg" controls="controls" preload="none"> <source src="movies/gantt-1.mp4"> Your browser does not support the HTML5 video tag </video> <h3>TeamHeadquarters Gantt Part 1 - Manually Adding Tasks</h3> <p>Instructional video on how to manually add tasks to a TeamHeadquarters project.</p></div><div class="media panel"> <video class="pull-right" width="320" height="240" poster="movies/gantt-2.jpg" controls="controls" preload="none"> <source src="movies/gantt-2.mp4"> Your browser does not support the HTML5 video tag </video> <h3>TeamHeadquarters Gantt Part 2 - Importing MS Project files and exporting too.</h3> <p>Instructional video on importing MS Project files into the TeamHeadquarters Gantt Chart. This video also shows you how to export files from TeamHeadquarters to MS Project.</p></div><div class="media panel"> <video class="pull-right" width="320" height="240" poster="movies/ticket-queues.jpg" controls="controls" preload="none"> <source src="movies/ticket-queues.mp4"> Your browser does not support the HTML5 video tag </video> <h3>TeamHeadquarters Queues</h3> <p>Instructional video on creating and managing TeamHeadquarters service desk queues.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div id="footer"> <?php include '../public_html/includes/footer.html';?> </div></body></html>